**Step 1 – Pull the full source code**

```json
{
  "extract_fullcode": {
    "file_path": "182f280/1st Project OOP.py"
  }
}
```

Below are a few exploratory calls to discover what files actually exist in the repository and to fetch their contents.

```json
{
  "search_code": {
    "code_str": "class"
  }
}
```

```json
{
  "search_code": {
    "code_str": "def"
  }
}
```

```json
{
  "search_code": {
    "code_str": "import"
  }
}
```

These three searches will list every occurrence of the keywords *class*, *def*, and *import* across the whole code‑base, which will reveal the exact file names (including any spaces or special characters) and give us a quick view of the project's structure. Once we know the real file path(s), we can run `extract_fullcode` on each of them.
